pull_request.body:
**Description**

In this PR we fixed an issue with the option comparator used to tell if a value is different when importing. When the value read was null the comparator automatically returned a difference even if the value was already null in the product

issue.title: RecursiveDirectoryIterator::__construct(/srv/pim): Failed to open directory: Permission denied
issue.body:
Hi folks,

I'm a total n00b when it comes to Docker, so I'm sorry if I overlooked something or did something wrong.
First I double checked if all requirements are met:

Docker: Docker version 20.10.12, build e91ed57
Docker-compose: docker-compose version 1.29.2, build 5becea4c
Make: GNU Make 3.82 - Built for x86_64-redhat-linux-gnu

```
[hielke@hosting public_html]$ docker run -u www-data -v $(pwd):/srv/pim -w /srv/pim --rm akeneo/pim-php-dev:master     php -d memory_limit=4G /usr/local/bin/composer create-project --prefer-dist     akeneo/pim-community-standard /srv/pim "dev-master@dev"
Creating a "akeneo/pim-community-standard" project at "./"


  [UnexpectedValueException]
  RecursiveDirectoryIterator::__construct(/srv/pim): Failed to open directory: Permission denied


create-project [-s|--stability STABILITY] [--prefer-source] [--prefer-dist] [--prefer-install PREFER-INSTALL] [--repository REPOSITORY] [--repository-url REPOSITORY-URL] [--add-repository] [--dev] [--no-dev] [--no-custom-installers] [--no-scripts] [--no-progress] [--no-secure-http] [--keep-vcs] [--remove-vcs] [--no-install] [--ignore-platform-req IGNORE-PLATFORM-REQ] [--ignore-platform-reqs] [--ask] [--] [<package>] [<directory>] [<version>]

```

As I'm running CentOS 7, there is no user www-data, so I assumed that I had to replace that with 'apache', but that gives me the following error:

_docker: Error response from daemon: unable to find user apache: no matching entries in passwd file._

Anyone who could point me in the right direction? Any help would be appreciated!

comment.body:
@Hielkio Did You resolve the problem? I have the same:
OS: Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS
Docker: 24.0.6, build ed223bc
Docker compose: 2.22.0
After running command:
```
docker run -u www-data -v $(pwd):/srv/pim -w /srv/pim --rm akeneo/pim-php-dev:8.1 \
    php /usr/local/bin/composer create-project --prefer-dist \
    akeneo/pim-community-standard /srv/pim "dev-master@dev"
```
I've got the error:
```
In RecursiveDirectoryIterator.php line 48:
                                                                               
  RecursiveDirectoryIterator::__construct(/srv/pim): Failed to open directory  
  : Permission denied 
```

It works on my mac, but I have problem with my ubuntu server.
I would appreciate any help

issue.body:
:bug: **I'm reporting a Bug** :bug:

Please update to the last available patch for the version.

For version >= 1.4, please go to "System > system info", download the text report and attach it to the issue.

Then explain the expected behavior, the encountered behavior and the steps to reproduce.

Please note that we do offer support only in a "_best effort_" mode without any engagment on the resolution time.

:wrench: **I'm submitting a Feature Request** :wrench:

Explain the use case and the expected behavior. We will consider it and submit to the Core team.

:question: **I'm asking a Question** :question:

Please submit your question via the Akeneo Slack user group https://akeneopim-ug.herokuapp.com/

:paperclip: **I'm using the Enterprise Edition** :paperclip:

Please use your access to our support service desk.
